["\ud83d\udcac I'll design this \u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1 protein. Let me start by checking what secondary structure conditioning options are available in RFdiffusion, then launch the first design.", "\ud83d\udd27 Agent({'subagent_type': 'Explore', 'description': 'Find secondary structure options', 'prompt': 'Search the RFdiffusion codeba)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(ls /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/)", "\ud83d\udd27 Glob({'pattern': '**/*.yaml'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Glob({'pattern': '**/*.yml'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Glob({'pattern': '**/*.py'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Glob({'pattern': '**/*.md'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(mkdir -p /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'secondary_structure|secondary-structure', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'helix|beta sheet|beta-sheet|strand', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion/config'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/config/inference/base.yaml)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/README.md)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'inpaint_str|secondary', 'type': 'py', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'helix|strand|sheet', 'type': 'py', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/contigs.py)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'get_inpaint_seq_str', 'type': 'py', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion', 'output_mode': 'content'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/contigs.py)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/helper_scripts/make_secstruc_adj.py)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'ss_spec|inpaint_str_helix|inpaint_str_strand|inpaint_str_loop', 'type': 'py', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusi)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/inference/utils.py)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'ss_from_contig|def ss_from_contig', 'type': 'py', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion', 'output_mode': 'content)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/inference/model_runners.py)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/inference/utils.py)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'Liu et al|2024.07.16', 'type': 'py', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion', 'output_mode': 'content'})", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(find /workspace/RFdiffusion -name \"*.md\" -type f -not -path \"*/.venv/*\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" -not -path \"*/.git/*\" | head -20)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/README.md)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(grep -r \"inpaint_str\" /workspace/RFdiffusion/examples/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"No examples found with inpaint_str\")", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(find /workspace/RFdiffusion -name \"*.sh\" -type f -not -path \"*/.venv/*\" | xargs grep -l \"inpaint_str\" 2>/dev/null | head -5)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/examples/design_ppi_flexible_peptide_with_secondarystructure_specification.sh)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/examples/design_ppi_flexible_peptide.sh)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(grep -r \"secondary\" /workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/ --include=\"*.py\" | grep -v \".pyc\" | head -20)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(grep -r \"helix\\|strand\\|loop\" /workspace/RFdiffusion --include=\"*.md\" | grep -v node_modules | head -10)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/workspace/README.md)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'scaffoldguided|scaffold_dir', 'type': 'py', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion', 'output_mode': 'c)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/config/inference/base.yaml)", "\ud83d\udcac Excellent! I have a clear plan. I'll use the **scaffoldguided** mode to specify the \u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1 topology with secondary structure tensors. Let me create the tensors and run the design.", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/examples/design_ppi_flexible_peptide_with_secondarystructure_specification.sh)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/helper_scripts/make_secstruc_adj.py)", "\ud83d\udcac Now I understand the scaffoldguided approach. Let me create the secondary structure tensors for the \u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1 topology and run the design.", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(python3 -c \"\nimport torch\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Define alpha-beta-alpha-beta-alpha topology (~86 residues)\n# Helix1(18) - Loop(4) - Strand1(8) - Loop(4) - Helix2(18) - Loop(4) - Strand2(8) - Loop(4) - Helix3(18)\n# SS encoding: 0=Helix, 1=Strand, 2=Loop\n\nsegments = [\n    (0, 18),  # Helix 1\n    (2, 4)", "\ud83d\udcac Now let me check what checkpoint is available and run the scaffoldguided design:", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(ls /workspace/RFdiffusion/models/)", "\ud83d\udd27 Grep({'pattern': 'Complex_Fold_base_ckpt|ckpt_override|scaffold.*ckpt', 'path': '/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/inference)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/inference/model_runners.py)", "\ud83d\udcac The scaffoldguided mode needs `Complex_Fold_base_ckpt.pt`. Let me check if I can download it:", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(grep -r \"Complex_Fold\" /workspace/RFdiffusion/scripts/ /workspace/RFdiffusion/README* /workspace/RFdiffusion/setup* 2>/dev/null | head -20)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(wget -q http://files.ipd.uw.edu/pub/RFdiffusion/60f09a193fb5e5ccdc4980417708dbab/Complex_Fold_base_ckpt.pt -O /workspace/RFdiffusion/models/Complex_Fold_base_ckpt.pt)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(ls -lh /workspace/RFdiffusion/models/Complex_Fold_base_ckpt.pt)", "\ud83d\udcac Got it. Now let me run the scaffoldguided design:", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(python3 scripts/run_inference.py \\\n  'contigmap.contigs=[86-86]' \\\n  scaffoldguided.scaffoldguided=True \\\n  scaffoldguided.target_ss=outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/design_ss.pt \\\n  scaffoldguided.target_adj=outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/design_adj.pt \\\n  scaffold)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/inference/model_runners.py)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/rfdiffusion/inference/model_runners.py)", "\ud83d\udcac I see \u2014 I need to use `scaffold_dir` instead of `target_ss`/`target_adj`. Let me restructure:", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(mkdir -p /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/scaffold && mv /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/design_ss.pt /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/scaffold/ && mv /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(python3 scripts/run_inference.py \\\n  'contigmap.contigs=[86-86]' \\\n  scaffoldguided.scaffoldguided=True \\\n  scaffoldguided.scaffold_dir=outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/scaffold \\\n  scaffoldguided.mask_loops=True \\\n  'potentials.guiding_potentials=[\"type:monomer_contacts,weight:0.2\"])", "\ud83d\udcac Design completed successfully! Let me verify the output and render it:", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(ls -la /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/design_0.*)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(head -30 /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/design_0.pdb)", "\ud83d\udcac Now let me render it with PyMOL, coloring by secondary structure to verify the \u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1 topology:", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(pymol -cq -d \"\nload /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/design_0.pdb;\nbg_color white;\nset ray_opaque_background, 1;\ncartoon automatic;\ncolor marine, ss h;\ncolor red, ss s;\ncolor gray80, ss l+'';\nset cartoon_fancy_helices, 1;\nset cartoon_flat_sheets_fancy, 1;\nray 8)", "\ud83d\udd27 Bash(pymol -cq -d \"\nload /workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/design_0.pdb;\nbg_color white;\nset ray_opaque_background, 1;\ncartoon automatic;\ncolor marine, ss H;\ncolor red, ss S;\ncolor gray80, ss L;\nset cartoon_fancy_helices, 1;\nray 800,600;\npng /workspace/RFdiffusion/ou)", "\ud83d\udd27 Read(/workspace/RFdiffusion/outputs/users/anonymous/b5bd337f/509fc8b7a5b0/v0/render.png)", "\ud83d\udcac \n\nThe design looks excellent! The v0 structure clearly shows the requested **\u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1-\u03b2-\u03b1 topology**:\n\n- **3 alpha helices** (blue) forming the structural scaffold\n- **2 beta strands** (red) forming a small antiparallel beta sheet in the center\n- **Loops** (white/gray) connecting the secondary structur", "\ud83c\udfc1 Done \u2014 turns=23 cost=$0.81887335"]